        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:08PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Overton, or 11 miles west of Kilgore, moving
southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tyler, Whitehouse, Overton, Troup, Arp and New Chapel Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
